In that he was not willing to arrogate the name of Christ he became a member of Christ. Because while he humbly strove to acknowledge his weakness, he in truth merited to obtain the loftiness. But with this reading, another saying of our Redeemer comes to mind, and in the words of that reading much bears before us. In that other place where the Lord was asked by the disciples about the coming of Elijah, he responded, "Elijah is already come, and they know him not, but have done unto him whatsoever they had a mind. And if you will know: John himself is Elijah."

